President Barack Obama has proclaimed October 2011 as National Arts and Humanities Month. The proclamation highlights the power of art to challenge perspectives and unite people. It acknowledges the contributions of artists and the economic importance of the arts industry. The proclamation also emphasizes the need to support arts education to foster critical and creative thinking in students. The arts and humanities are recognized as tools for breaking social and political barriers and driving towards a more perfect union. The President calls upon the people of the United States to observe the month with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs to celebrate the arts and humanities in America.